Have you always wanted
to climb the mountains of Mars...

87
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:44,353
but now you're over the hill?

88
00:09:45,697 --> 00:09:47,597
Then come to Rekall lncorporated...

89
00:09:47,665 --> 00:09:50,725
where you can buy the memory
of your ideal vacation...

90
00:09:50,802 --> 00:09:53,464
cheaper, safer and better
than the real thing.

91
00:09:53,538 --> 00:09:56,302
So don't let life pass you by.

92
00:09:56,374 --> 00:09:59,969
Call Rekall
for the memory of a lifetime.

93
00:10:00,044 --> 00:10:03,946
For the memory of a lifetime

94
00:10:04,015 --> 00:10:07,416
Rekall, Rekall, Rekall

95
00:10:26,237 --> 00:10:27,329
Harry.

96
00:10:30,742 --> 00:10:33,108
- You ever hear of Rekall?
- Rekall?

97
00:10:33,178 --> 00:10:35,112
Where they sell
those fake memories.

98
00:10:35,180 --> 00:10:36,670
Oh, Rekall.

99
00:10:39,350 --> 00:10:41,477
- Thinking of going there?
- Maybe.

100
00:10:41,553 --> 00:10:43,487
- Well, don't.
- Why not?

101
00:10:43,555 --> 00:10:48,083
A friend of mine tried it,
nearly got himself lobotomized.

102
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:50,022
No shit?

103
00:10:50,094 --> 00:10:52,858
Don't fuck with your brain.
It ain't worth it.

104
00:10:54,666 --> 00:10:56,600
I guess not.

105
00:11:40,912 --> 00:11:43,346
Good afternoon.
Welcome to Rekall.

106
00:11:43,414 --> 00:11:45,507
Douglas Quaid.
I have an appointment.

107
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,410
- Bob?
- Yeah?

108
00:11:50,488 --> 00:11:53,548
- Doug Quaid is here to see you.
- I'll be right out.

109
00:11:54,626 --> 00:11:56,423
Just one minute, Mr. Quaid.

110
00:11:57,595 --> 00:11:59,028
Thank you.

111
00:12:07,639 --> 00:12:10,199
- Paul McClane. Good to see you.
- Nice to meet you.

112
00:12:10,275 --> 00:12:11,902
Come on in.

113
00:12:13,544 --> 00:12:15,774
- Make yourself comfortable.
- Thank you.

114
00:12:16,848 --> 00:12:18,577
Help me out here, Doug.

115
00:12:18,650 --> 00:12:21,380
- You were interested in a memory of--
- Mars.

116
00:12:22,453 --> 00:12:24,114
Yeah. Mars.

117
00:12:24,188 --> 00:12:25,621
Is there a problem?

118
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:29,286
To be perfectly honest...

119
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,884
if you like outer space...

120
00:12:30,962 --> 00:12:35,524
you'd be happier with
one of our Saturn cruises.

121
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:38,433
I'm not interested in Saturn.
I said Mars.

122
00:12:39,304 --> 00:12:40,999
Okay. You're the boss.

123
00:12:42,073 --> 00:12:44,132
Mars it is.

124
00:12:44,842 --> 00:12:46,503
Now, let me see.

125
00:12:46,577 --> 00:12:48,636
The basic Mars package...

126
00:12:48,713 --> 00:12:52,046
will run you 899 credits.

127
00:12:52,116 --> 00:12:55,574
Now, that's for two full weeks
of memories, complete in every detail.

128
00:12:55,653 --> 00:12:59,145
A longer trip is more expensive
because it's a deeper implant.

129
00:12:59,223 --> 00:13:01,657
What's in the two-week package?

130
00:13:01,726 --> 00:13:05,287
When you go Rekall, you get nothing
but first-class memories.

131
00:13:06,431 --> 00:13:10,424
Private shuttle cabin, deluxe suite
at the Hilton, all the major sights:

132
00:13:10,501 --> 00:13:12,833
Mount Pyramid,
the Grand Canals...

133
00:13:12,904 --> 00:13:15,429
and, of course, Venusville.

134
00:13:15,506 --> 00:13:17,303
But how real does it seem?

135
00:13:17,375 --> 00:13:21,607
- As real as any memory in your head.
- Don't bullshit me.

136
00:13:21,679 --> 00:13:24,614
I'm telling you, your brain
will not know the difference.

137
00:13:24,682 --> 00:13:26,741
That's guaranteed
or your money back.

138
00:13:26,818 --> 00:13:30,151
What about the guy you lobotomized?
Did he get a refund?

139
00:13:33,791 --> 00:13:35,850
You're talking ancient history.

140
00:13:35,927 --> 00:13:39,920
Nowadays traveling with Rekall
is safer than getting on a rocket.

141
00:13:39,997 --> 00:13:41,931
Check out those statistics.

142
00:13:41,999 --> 00:13:45,696
Besides, a real holiday
is a pain in the butt.

143
00:13:45,770 --> 00:13:48,432
You got lost luggage,
lousy weather...

144
00:13:48,506 --> 00:13:50,497
crooked taxi drivers.

145
00:13:50,575 --> 00:13:52,770
When you travel with Rekall...

146
00:13:52,844 --> 00:13:55,870
everything is perfect.

147
00:13:55,947 --> 00:13:57,039
What do you say?

148
00:13:59,217 --> 00:14:02,015
- All right.
- Smart move.

149
00:14:02,086 --> 00:14:05,419
While you fill out
this questionnaire,

150
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:08,015
I'll familiarize you
with some of our options.

151
00:14:08,092 --> 00:14:09,559
No options.

152
00:14:10,762 --> 00:14:14,129
Whatever you say.
Let me ask you one question.

153
00:14:14,966 --> 00:14:16,991
What is exactly the same...

154
00:14:17,068 --> 00:14:20,231
about every single vacation
you have ever taken?

155
00:14:21,439 --> 00:14:22,531
I give up.

156
00:14:22,607 --> 00:14:25,371
You. You're the same.

157
00:14:25,443 --> 00:14:28,003
No matter where you go,
it's always you.

158
00:14:28,913 --> 00:14:31,438
Let me suggest
that you take a vacation...

159
00:14:31,516 --> 00:14:32,915
from yourself.

160
00:14:32,984 --> 00:14:34,576
I know, it sounds wild.

161
00:14:34,652 --> 00:14:37,587
It is the latest thing in travel.
We call it the Ego Trip.

162
00:14:38,322 --> 00:14:39,812
I'm not interested.

163
00:14:39,891 --> 00:14:41,688
You're gonna love this, Doug.

164
00:14:41,759 --> 00:14:45,456
We offer you a choice of
alternate identities during your trip.

165
00:14:45,530 --> 00:14:49,091
Why go to Mars as a tourist
when you can go as a playboy...

166
00:14:49,167 --> 00:14:51,032
or a famous jock or--

167
00:14:51,102 --> 00:14:52,228
"Secret agent."

168
00:14:52,303 --> 00:14:54,066
How much is that?

169
00:14:57,141 --> 00:14:59,507
Let me tantalize you.

170
00:14:59,577 --> 00:15:04,378
You are a top operative under deep cover
on your most important mission.

171
00:15:04,449 --> 00:15:07,043
People are trying to kill you.

172
00:15:07,118 --> 00:15:10,383
You meet this beautiful,
exotic woman.

173
00:15:10,455 --> 00:15:11,547
Go on.

174
00:15:11,622 --> 00:15:14,284
I don't wanna spoil it for you...

175
00:15:14,358 --> 00:15:16,553
but by the time
the trip is over...

176
00:15:16,627 --> 00:15:20,620
you get the girl, kill the bad guys
and save the entire planet.

177
00:15:20,698 --> 00:15:22,188
Now, you tell me.

178
00:15:22,266 --> 00:15:25,201
Isn't that worth
a measly 300 credits?

179
00:15:39,617 --> 00:15:40,845
Your first trip?

180
00:15:42,153 --> 00:15:45,088
Don't worry. Things hardly ever
fuck up around here.

181
00:15:46,290 --> 00:15:48,315
Good evening... Doug.

182
00:15:48,392 --> 00:15:50,758
- I'm Dr. Lull.
- Nice to meet you.

183
00:15:50,828 --> 00:15:54,628
Ernie, patch in matrix 62-B-37.

184
00:15:54,699 --> 00:15:57,634
Would you like us to integrate
some alien stuff?

185
00:15:57,702 --> 00:15:59,636
Sure. Why not?

186
00:16:01,239 --> 00:16:02,672
Two-headed monsters?

187
00:16:02,740 --> 00:16:04,674
Don't you watch the news?

188
00:16:04,742 --> 00:16:08,303
- We're doing alien artifacts now.
- It's wild.

189
00:16:08,379 --> 00:16:11,280
Yeah, they date back
a million years.

190
00:16:12,583 --> 00:16:14,312
- Ernie?
- That's a new one.

191
00:16:14,385 --> 00:16:16,182
- Blue sky on Mars.
- Been married long?

192
00:16:17,255 --> 00:16:19,723
- Eight years.
- Oh, I see.

193
00:16:19,790 --> 00:16:22,281
Slipping away for
a little hanky-panky.

194
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:25,158
- No. I'm fascinated with Mars.
- All systems go.

195
00:16:25,229 --> 00:16:27,129
Number seven.

196
00:16:27,198 --> 00:16:28,631
Ready for dreamland?

197
00:16:31,202 --> 00:16:35,366
I'll be asking you some questions
so we can fine-tune the Ego program.

198
00:16:35,439 --> 00:16:38,374
You answer honestly,
you'll enjoy yourself much more.

199
00:16:38,442 --> 00:16:41,309
- Your sexual orientation.
- Hetero.

200
00:16:46,784 --> 00:16:48,809
How do you like your women?

201
00:16:48,886 --> 00:16:51,821
Blonde? Brunette? Redhead?

202
00:16:52,657 --> 00:16:53,954
Brunette.

203
00:16:56,227 --> 00:17:00,186
Slim. Athletic. Voluptuous.

204
00:17:03,601 --> 00:17:05,034
Athletic.

205
00:17:09,340 --> 00:17:13,242
Demure. Aggressive. Sleazy.

206
00:17:13,311 --> 00:17:14,835
Be honest.

207
00:17:14,912 --> 00:17:16,345
Sleazy.

208
00:17:20,718 --> 00:17:21,980
Demure.

209
00:17:24,655 --> 00:17:26,088
41A, Ernie.

210
00:17:27,959 --> 00:17:30,052
Boy, is he gonna have
a wild time.

211
00:17:31,062 --> 00:17:34,589
- He's not gonna want to come back.
- That's for sure.

212
00:17:55,820 --> 00:17:56,912
So...

213
00:17:56,988 --> 00:17:58,888
what do you say?

214
00:17:58,956 --> 00:18:01,891
I'm not so sure,
and I don't get a souvenir.

215
00:18:01,959 --> 00:18:07,363
Not true. We supply T-shirts,
snapshots of you at the site...

216
00:18:07,431 --> 00:18:09,365
and even letters from--

217
00:18:12,703 --> 00:18:14,898
- What is it?
- Get down here.

218
00:18:14,972 --> 00:18:17,304
I am with
a very important client.

219
00:18:17,375 --> 00:18:19,809
Looks like we got
another schizoid embolism.

220
00:18:21,512 --> 00:18:23,139
I'll be right back.

221
00:18:23,214 --> 00:18:24,306
Mr. McClane?

222
00:18:26,083 --> 00:18:27,812
Bob! What's wrong?

223
00:18:27,885 --> 00:18:29,819
Don't let her leave!

224
00:18:34,525 --> 00:18:36,322
Get off!

225
00:18:38,195 --> 00:18:39,958
You blew my cover!

226
00:18:40,031 --> 00:18:43,228
You can't do a simple
goddamn double implant?

227
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:44,961
We hit a memory cap.

228
00:18:45,036 --> 00:18:47,368
They're coming!
They'll kill you all!

229
00:18:47,438 --> 00:18:50,168
- What is he talking about?
- Let me go!

230
00:18:50,241 --> 00:18:52,141
Mr. Quaid, try to calm down!

231
00:18:54,645 --> 00:18:56,579
My name is not Quaid.

232
00:18:56,647 --> 00:19:00,515
- Let me go! Untie me now!
- Ernie, grab his leg!

233
00:19:00,584 --> 00:19:03,075
- Hold him down!
- Let me go!

234
00:19:26,811 --> 00:19:29,075
Are you all right?

235
00:19:29,146 --> 00:19:32,274
Listen to me.
He's been going on and on about Mars.

236
00:19:32,349 --> 00:19:35,284
- He has really been there.
- Use your head.

237
00:19:35,352 --> 00:19:38,651
He's just acting out the "secret agent"
portion of his ego trip.

238
00:19:38,723 --> 00:19:40,657
- That's not possible.
- Why not?

239
00:19:40,725 --> 00:19:42,522
We haven't implanted it yet.

240
00:19:46,764 --> 00:19:48,026
Oh, shit.

241
00:19:49,633 --> 00:19:53,228
I've been trying to tell you,
someone has erased his memory.

242
00:19:53,304 --> 00:19:54,566
Excuse me.

243
00:19:54,638 --> 00:19:56,401
"Someone"?

244
00:19:56,474 --> 00:19:58,408
We're talking about the Agency.

245
00:19:58,476 --> 00:20:01,172
- Shut up!
- Bob, the client's gone.

246
00:20:03,647 --> 00:20:07,242
Renata, cover up any memory he's got
of us or Rekall.

247
00:20:07,318 --> 00:20:09,548
I'll try.
It's pretty messy in there.

248
00:20:09,620 --> 00:20:12,851
Ernie, dump him in a cab.
Tiffany, you help him.

249
00:20:12,923 --> 00:20:15,915
I'm gonna destroy his file
and refund his money.

250
00:20:15,993 --> 00:20:19,326
And if anybody comes asking,
we never heard of Douglas Quaid.

251
00:20:33,744 --> 00:20:35,177
Where am l?

252
00:20:37,515 --> 00:20:39,449
You're in a Johnnycab.

253
00:20:39,517 --> 00:20:41,109
